            <div corresp="#c0105f2">
                <head>Archangel</head>
                <p>Wm Brandt, Jr. (brother of Consul) acted as Consul (absence of Consul) Dec. 1833?
                    to 1836?</p>
                <p>Edw Brandt signs for the Consul (no despatches 1836-1841) Jan. 1841 to Jan.
                    1848.</p>
                <p>George Mallison signs for Consul Brandt as Secretary Jan. 1849 to Dec. 1850.</p>
                <p>Charles Brandt " " Edmund " " (no despatches 1850 to 1853) Apr. 1853 to Jan.
                    1856.</p>
                <p>R. Finch " " " " in despatch dated March 1857</p>
                <p>E.H. Brandt " " " " Jan. 1858 to Jan. 1859.</p>
                <p>Charles Brandt " " " " despatch dated Jan. 1860.</p>
                <p>E.H. Brandt " " " " Jan. 1861 (last despatch)</p>
                <p>R. Lindes writes as Consul - Oct. 1889.</p>
                <p>Ferd Lindes declines to give bond - March 13, 1894 - last despatch</p>
                <p>Shelby P. Strother, Consul, Cl 8, was detailed to Archangel and arrived there
                    Aug. 9, 1919; detailed to Helsingfors Apr. 15, 1919; turned office over to
                    Consul Strother May 15, 1919.</p>
                <p>Leald A. Davis, from Hartford, Conn., appointed V.C. at Archangel Oct. 4, 1917,
                    and promoted to Consul Feb. 19, 1918 (<unclear>Consulate closed Sept. 13,
                        1919</unclear>).</p>
                <p>Felix Cole, who was appointed U.S.C. at Archangel Oct. 4, 1917, took over the
                    office from Consul Davis Dec. 31, 1918, and ordered Aug. 6, 1919 to return to
                    U.S.A. Left 9/14/1919.</p>
            </div>
